<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="966" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d966">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9393:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-28T18:00:00-05:00">March 28,
                                    1941—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>58. Your 252, March 27, midnight. Since this Government has never
                            withdrawn recognition of the monarchy there is no special action
                            required for recognition of the new Cabinet under Premier Simović set up
                            by King Peter. Therefore the specific question raised in your telegram
                            does not arise.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>